Thailand police have offered a £13,000 reward in their hunt for the killers of two British tourists. 

The bodies of David Miller, 24, and Hannah Witheridge, 23, were found on a beach on the island of Koh Tao on September 15. 

A bloodstained garden hoe, believed to be the murder weapon, was found nearby.

