Post-mortem examinations showed that Miss Witheridge, from Great Yarmouth, Norfolk, died from head wounds, while Mr Miller, from Jersey, died after severe blows to the head and drowning.

Around 150 police officers were posted to Koh Tao as part of the murder investigation but detectives are apparently no closer to finding the killer.

Thai police have been criticised for leading a chaotic investigation into the deaths of the tourists in which the line of inquiry has changed several times.

More than 170 DNA samples have so far been taken, the Bangkok Post reported on Thursday. 

